about.description:
Quart-Trio is an extension for Quart to support the Trio event loop.
This is an alternative to using the asyncio event loop present in the Python
standard library and supported by default in Quart.
about.summary: Quart-Trio is an extension for Quart to support the Trio event loop

name: quart-trio
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Quart-Trio" %}
{% set version = "0.5.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 136bcf0412fea3c96f8215324dc00abcfd609a1cbb13e8d8d0c0295c61dad3ad

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7.0
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.7.0
    - quart >=0.11.1
    - trio >=0.10.0
    - hypercorn >=0.6.0

test:
  imports:
    - quart_trio

about:
  home: https://gitlab.com/pgjones/quart-trio
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Quart-Trio is an extension for Quart to support the Trio event loop'
  description: |
    Quart-Trio is an extension for Quart to support the Trio event loop.
    This is an alternative to using the asyncio event loop present in the Python
    standard library and supported by default in Quart.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - scopatz
